<H2 class=3Dsmalll><A name=3Dnotes>Disclaimer and Validity Notes</A> =
</H2>
<P class=3Dsmallj>No guarantee can be given for the dates computed, as =
errors are=20
always possible. If the result of a conversion is critical, or money, =
time, or=20
workforce is to be spent depending on a conversion, further sources must =
be=20
consulted to check the dates. </P>
<P class=3Dsmallj>No range checking is carried out. On the results =
window, check=20
the date entered (printed with bold letters). For instance, a date=20
32&nbsp;December 1999 will be treated as 1 January 2000. </P>
<P class=3Dsmallj>Gregorian dates before 15&nbsp;October 1582 will be =
computed but=20
given italic as this calendar was not used before that date. </P>
<P class=3Dsmallj>Dates of the Julian calendar before 1&nbsp;January =
8&nbsp;CE=20
will be printed italic because there have been some irregularities in =
the use of=20
the calendar before the year 761&nbsp;a.&nbsp;u.&nbsp;c., which was our=20
8&nbsp;CE. For the same reason, Roman dates before the calends of =
January=20
761&nbsp;a.&nbsp;u.&nbsp;c. (1&nbsp;January 8&nbsp;CE) will not be =
given. </P>
<P class=3Dsmallj>The Jewish Calendar was fixed around the 10th century. =
Thus,=20
Jewish calendar dates up to the 10th century are printed in italic =
letters as=20
they probably do not correspond to the dates then used. An Adar&nbsp;II =
given in=20
common years will be treated as Adar. </P>
<P class=3Dsmallj>In France, the Revolutionary calendar was officially =
used from=20
24&nbsp;November&nbsp;1793 until 31&nbsp;Dezember&nbsp;1805, inclusive. =
However,=20
it is possible to compute the dates of the Revolutionary calendar from=20
22&nbsp;September&nbsp;1792 (which was - in theory - 1 =
Vend=E9miaire&nbsp;I) until=20
22&nbsp;September&nbsp;1806 (which would have been the =
5th&nbsp;complementary=20
day&nbsp;XIV, had the calendar not been abolished). Dates that can be =
computed=20
but are not in the period in which the calendar was valid are printed =
italic.=20
</P>
<P class=3Dsmallj>Mayan calendar dates are computed according to the=20
Goodman-Martinez-Thompson correlation. The Mayan date 0&nbsp;Pictun=20
0&nbsp;Baktun 0&nbsp;Katun 0&nbsp;Tun 0&nbsp;Uinal 0&nbsp;Kin is =
considered to=20
correspond to 6&nbsp;September 3114&nbsp;BCE (Julian). This day is =
described by=20
Tzolkin date 4&nbsp;Ahau and Haab date 8&nbsp;Cumku; at least in this =
point the=20
different correlations agree. By leaving aside the larger Mayan time =
units=20
Calabtun, Kinchiltun, and Alautun, the supported range is "limited" to =
Julian=20
dates (JD) between 584283 and 58184282, inclusively. </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=3Dsmalll>Remarks</P>
<DIV class=3Dremark>
<P class=3Dremarkj><A name=3D01></A>*<BR>
<P class=3Dremarkj>The date is calculated according to a schematic =
version of the=20
Islamic calendar with the era 16&nbsp;July 622&nbsp;CE. Of a =
30-year-cycle, the=20
2nd, 5th, 7th, 10th, 13th, 16th, 18th, 21th, 24th, 26th, and 29th years =
are leap=20
years. </P>
